<br>
He also dispells, so typically on the raids I have been on you start of with four crap buffs.  These are things like poison resist, see invis, resist disease, etc.  Then you buff the more important buffs, cleric HP &amp; AC buffs, Shammy STA &amp; HP buffs, and FR buffs.<br>
<br>
Its also to good to have 3 or 4 enchanters available to siphon his mana.  Basically the plan of attack goes something like this.  The main tank (usually the highest level with the most AC, HP, and resists) rushes Naggy and gets his attention, turning his tail toward the door.  The other melee follow in very soon after.  No one taunts but the main tank, unless he goes down.  The main tank needs to get solid agro.  As people get low on health, they dart back towards the door to the lair and get heals.  The casters sit in the safe room outside his lair and wait.  And wait.  And wait.  Once Naggy is at half health, they get called in to start nuking.  You have to be within melee range for nukes to work on him, I believe.  If all has gone well to this point, he usually goes down fast.<br>
<br>
Now, this doesn't detail what needs to be done to kill all the Fire Giants on the way to Naggy's lair, or how to get the Fire Giants out of his lair before you rush him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umorphiusthejeweller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorphiusTheJeweller</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/7/01 11:57:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Naggy Raid for the epic piece</span><hr size=1> Naggy doesn't have mana, so no need for an enchanter on raid except to buff.<br>
